<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 08 at 5:58AM CST  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG AFFECTING THE REGION...
Surface observations indicate that areas of fog are affecting
Deep South Texas and the Rio Grande Valley at this time. Traffic
cameras suggest that this fog is very shallow, extending from
the surface to a few dozen feet above the ground. All of this
fog is the result of a moist atmosphere interacting with clear
skies and calm to very light winds.
Motorists can expect visibilities between one quarter of a mile
and two miles in any fog through the next couple of hours. Use
low beam headlights, reduce speed, and avoid tailgating while
commuting to work or school this morning.</description>
